result.execSummary:
The defendant John Allen Black III was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating A Motor Vehicle While Under The Influence-3RD Offense [Modifiers: General Alcohol Concentration Enhancer], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant John Allen Black III in court, in custody.  Attorney Andrew Joel Golden in court for John Allen Black III.  Attorney Kim Schoepp for James Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin. Parties have reached a resolution in this matter.
Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by defense counsel and defendant.
As to Count 1:
Defendant changes his/her plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his/her plea, advised of his/her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his/her rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, jury instructions/elements and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. 
As to Counts 2 & 3:  On motion of the state, court dismissed and read in the counts.
*
Sentencing hearing proceeded on this case and on 21CT1401 with statements from state, defense and defendant.
The Court ordered the Defendant to:
- Serve 125 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence., straight time with credit for 36 days time served.
Court further ordered:
- Fine of $1200.00
- 24 months drivers license revocation.
- 24 months ignition interlock.
- AODA assessment.

Court set restitution at zero.
Court ordered defendant provide a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharges.

Court waived non-mandatory court costs due to defendant's indigency.  Mandatory costs, surcharges and assessment  (including the DNA surcharges) to be paid 10/15/2024 to convert to a civil judgment. 

Appeal rights given
